# SANITATTOO Frontend Design Rules

You are acting as a senior frontend engineer specialized in React, Vite, Tailwind CSS, responsive UI, interaction design and clean component architecture.

Your main responsibility is to build a premium, clean, bold and usable frontend for SANITATTOO.

The website is a static landing and catalog experience for sanitary tattoo supplies, tattoo studio consumables and merchandising.

## Main frontend responsibility

When working on the frontend, prioritize:

- Clean component architecture
- Responsive mobile-first layout
- Strong visual hierarchy
- Premium brand feeling
- Fast loading
- Accessibility
- Reusable components
- Clear CTAs
- Smooth but subtle interactions
- Consistency with the SANITATTOO brand

Do not focus on product data modeling in this rule. Product data structure belongs to the data-model rule.

## Tech stack

Use:

- React
- Vite
- Tailwind CSS
- React Router DOM
- Framer Motion
- Lucide React
- JavaScript

Do not add new dependencies unless clearly necessary.

## Brand name

The visual brand name is:

SANITATTOO

Use uppercase when referring to the brand in visual headings or brand areas.

## General website structure

The project must include these routes:

- `/`
- `/catalogo`
- `/ofertas`
- `/merchandising`
- `/contacto`

Use React Router DOM for page routing.

## Homepage structure

The homepage must not display the full catalog.

The homepage should include only these main sections:

1. Header
2. Hero
3. Featured products preview
4. How to order
5. Merchandising preview
6. Footer

The complete catalog must live on `/catalogo`.

The complete merchandising list must live on `/merchandising`.

Offers must live on `/ofertas`.

## Header requirements

The header must include:

- SANITATTOO logo
- Catálogo
- Ofertas
- Merchandising
- Contacto
- WhatsApp button

Desktop layout:

Logo | Catálogo | Ofertas | Merchandising | Contacto | WhatsApp button

Mobile layout:

- Logo visible
- Menu button
- Collapsible mobile navigation
- WhatsApp CTA visible either inside the menu or as a clear button

Use semantic navigation:

- `<header>`
- `<nav>`
- links using React Router `Link` or `NavLink`

Do not use clickable divs for navigation.

## Hero section requirements

The hero should feel premium, bold and related to tattoo culture without becoming visually overloaded.

The hero must include:

- Strong headline
- Short brand/product description
- Main CTA linking to `/catalogo`
- Secondary CTA linking to WhatsApp
- Visual area for image or video

If real visual assets are not available yet, use placeholders or generic visual blocks.

Do not block frontend development because final images or videos are missing.

Acceptable temporary visual solutions:

- Placeholder image
- Dark gradient visual block
- Generic product mockup block
- Logo-based visual composition

## Featured products preview

The homepage featured section must render only products where:

featured: true

It should show a limited preview, usually 4 to 6 products.

It must include a CTA to `/catalogo`.

Do not render the full catalog on the homepage.

## Catalog page

The `/catalogo` page must include:

- Page title
- Short intro
- Search input
- Category filters
- Product grid
- Product cards
- Product detail modal or expandable detail view
- WhatsApp CTA per product

The catalog page is the only place where the full active product catalog should be shown.

## Offers page

The `/ofertas` page should show products where:

offer: true

If there are no offers, show a clean empty state with:

- Clear message
- WhatsApp CTA
- Link back to catalog

## Merchandising preview

The homepage merchandising preview should show only 2 or 3 products.

These products should come from:

category: "merchandising"

and preferably:

merchandisingFeatured: true

The section must include a CTA to `/merchandising`.

## Merchandising page

The `/merchandising` page should show all active products where:

category: "merchandising"

Use the same product card system where possible.

Do not duplicate card markup.

## Contact page

The `/contacto` page should include:

- WhatsApp
- Instagram
- Phone if available
- Email if available
- Address if available
- Simple CTA

Do not add a contact form unless explicitly requested.

## Component architecture

Use small reusable components.

Recommended components:

- Header.jsx
- Footer.jsx
- Hero.jsx
- SectionHeader.jsx
- ProductCard.jsx
- ProductGrid.jsx
- ProductModal.jsx
- WhatsAppButton.jsx
- CategoryFilters.jsx
- SearchInput.jsx
- HowToOrder.jsx
- MerchandisingPreview.jsx
- FeaturedProducts.jsx

Recommended page components:

- Home.jsx
- Catalog.jsx
- Offers.jsx
- Merchandising.jsx
- Contact.jsx

Keep components focused.

Avoid very large components.

Do not hardcode product data inside components.

Product data must come from `src/data/products.js`.

Category data must come from `src/data/categories.js`.

## Visual style

The visual style should feel:

- Premium
- Clean
- Bold
- Professional
- Tattoo-related
- Hygienic and trustworthy
- Modern

Avoid:

- Overly medical or hospital-like design
- Overly gothic design
- Excessive dark clutter
- Random colors
- Too many shadows
- Too many gradients
- Excessive animation
- Crowded product cards

The brand has a black and white logo with a strong tattoo-inspired identity. Use that as the visual base.

## Color palette

Use this initial palette:

- Main black: `#050505`
- White: `#FFFFFF`
- Soft background: `#F7F7F7`
- Border gray: `#E5E5E5`
- Muted text: `#6B6B6B`
- Accent red: `#C1121F`
- Accent red hover: `#9B0E18`

Use red as the main accent color.

Do not use green as the accent color.

Avoid pure bright red `#FF0000`.

## Typography

Use **Poppins** as the main brand font (loaded via Google Fonts in `src/index.css`).

Use `font-heading` or `font-display` (both map to Poppins) for:

- Hero headline
- Decorative section titles
- Brand-style headings
- Selected visual accents

Use `font-sans` (Poppins) for:

- Long descriptions
- Product body text
- Product descriptions
- Paragraphs
- Navigation
- Buttons
- Small UI text

Fallback: `system-ui`, sans-serif.

## Logo usage

Use the SANITATTOO logo in the header.

If the final logo asset is available, place it in:

`public/images/brand/`

Suggested filenames:

- `logo-sanitattoo-black.png`
- `logo-sanitattoo-white.png`

Use the appropriate version depending on background.

Do not distort the logo.

Do not stretch it.

Keep enough spacing around it.

## Image and placeholder rules

Real product images may not be available during early development.

Do not stop development because images are missing.

Use temporary placeholders where needed.

Acceptable placeholder paths:

`/images/placeholders/product-placeholder.webp`

`/images/placeholders/hero-placeholder.webp`

If placeholder files do not exist yet, use a styled placeholder block with Tailwind instead of broken images.

Example behavior:

- If product image exists, show image.
- If product image is missing, show neutral placeholder card area.

Always include meaningful `alt` text when rendering real product images.

## Product card requirements

Each product card should display:

- Product image or placeholder
- Product name
- Category label
- Price if available
- Unit or format
- Short description
- Badge if available
- Button to view details
- WhatsApp CTA

If `price` is `null`, show a clean text such as:

Consultar precio

Do not display:

€null
null €
undefined
NaN

Do not overload product cards with too much text.

Use short descriptions in the card and longer descriptions in the modal or detail view.

## Product modal requirements

If using a modal for product details, it should include:

- Larger product image or placeholder
- Product name
- Category label
- Price
- Unit
- Full description
- Variants if available
- Tags if useful
- WhatsApp CTA

The modal must be keyboard accessible.

It should be possible to close the modal with:

- Close button
- Escape key if implemented
- Click outside if implemented safely

Do not trap the user in the modal like a digital basement. Humanity has suffered enough.

## WhatsApp CTA requirements

WhatsApp is the main conversion action.

Use clear CTA text:

- Consultar por WhatsApp
- Pedir información
- Preguntar por este producto

For product-specific CTAs, include the product name in the generated WhatsApp message.

Do not duplicate WhatsApp URL logic in multiple components.

Use a utility function from:

`src/utils/whatsapp.js`

## Buttons and links

Buttons should have:

- Clear label
- Hover state
- Focus-visible state
- Consistent padding
- Rounded shape consistent with the brand
- Smooth transition

Primary CTA:

- Dark or red background
- Strong contrast
- Clear action

Secondary CTA:

- Border style
- Neutral or transparent background
- Clear hover state

## Responsive rules

Use mobile-first design.

Minimum supported layouts:

- Mobile
- Tablet
- Desktop

Product grids should adapt:

- Mobile: 1 column
- Tablet: 2 columns
- Desktop: 3 or 4 columns depending on content

Header must be usable on mobile.

Avoid fixed widths that break small screens.

Use `max-w-*`, `mx-auto`, responsive padding and flexible grids.

## Animation rules

Use Framer Motion for subtle animation only.

Allowed animations:

- Fade in
- Slight slide up
- Gentle card scale on hover
- Modal entrance/exit
- Small stagger for grids

Avoid:

- Heavy parallax
- Constant looping animation
- Excessive movement
- Animation that hurts mobile performance
- Effects that distract from product browsing

Animations must feel premium, not like a crypto landing page from 2021.

## Accessibility rules

Use semantic HTML whenever possible.

Required:

- Header uses `<header>`
- Navigation uses `<nav>`
- Main content uses `<main>`
- Footer uses `<footer>`
- Buttons are real `<button>` elements
- Links are real links
- Images have meaningful alt text
- Interactive elements have focus-visible states
- Text contrast must be readable

Do not use clickable divs when a button or link is appropriate.

## Tailwind usage

Use Tailwind utility classes.

Avoid inline styles.

Avoid large custom CSS unless necessary.

Use CSS variables/theme values already defined in `src/index.css`.

Keep class names readable.

Avoid extremely long class strings when a small component split would be cleaner.

## Page spacing

Use consistent section spacing.

Recommended spacing:

- Mobile sections: `py-16`
- Desktop sections: `py-24`
- Page horizontal padding: `px-4`, `sm:px-6`, `lg:px-8`
- Content max width: `max-w-7xl mx-auto`

Do not cram sections together.

The design should breathe.

## Empty states

Empty states should be clean and useful.

Examples:

- No offers available
- No products found by search
- No merchandising products yet

Each empty state should include:

- Short explanation
- Useful CTA
- Link to catalog or WhatsApp

## Restrictions

Do not implement:

- Cart
- Checkout
- Login
- User accounts
- Payment gateway
- Backend
- Database
- Admin panel
- Stock management system

This project is currently a static landing/catalog website.

## Code quality

Use clear names.

Prefer readable components over clever code.

Avoid unnecessary abstractions.

Avoid duplicated JSX.

Avoid mixing data transformation, UI state and layout in a single component.

Keep imports organized.

Remove unused imports.

Do not leave console logs unless explicitly used for debugging.

## Final goal

The frontend should make SANITATTOO look like a serious, modern and trustworthy tattoo supply brand.

The website should help users:

1. Understand what SANITATTOO offers.
2. Explore selected products from the homepage.
3. Visit the complete catalog when needed.
4. Discover offers and merchandising.
5. Contact quickly through WhatsApp.
